{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886436048,"sessionID":"ses_284ed1db4ffef84KWPn8fGNBw4","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1486a5001CgeZGR4YlHFNPW","messageID":"msg_d7b147966001rJqAJLbSQj83WV","sessionID":"ses_284ed1db4ffef84KWPn8fGNBw4","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_tool-d94079699b57486594142b4046472e73","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"grep -E \"docker-buildx-push|gen-check|gen-copyright|e2e|e2e-clean\" changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md | head -20","description":"Search for specific targets in AR-033 spec"},"output":"","metadata":{"output":"","exit":0,"description":"Search for specific targets in AR-033 spec","truncated":false},"title":"Search for specific targets in AR-033 spec","time":{"start":1775886436032,"end":1775886436047}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886436052,"sessionID":"ses_284ed1db4ffef84KWPn8fGNBw4","part":{"id":"prt_d7b14834b001cvIe41o8BRzspy","messageID":"msg_d7b147966001rJqAJLbSQj83WV","sessionID":"ses_284ed1db4ffef84KWPn8fGNBw4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f8a938aec5fe4da2a59d338b81d926c8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系 Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## AR Metadata\n4: - **AR ID**: AR-033\n5: - **Title**: Makefile 构建目标体系\n6: - **Module**: root\n7: - **Language**: Makefile\n8: - **Size**: M\n9: - **Status**: Implementation Required\n10: \n11: ## Purpose\n12: \n13: This delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for the Makefile build target system in the AgentCube project. It defines requirements for a unified build system that manages building, testing, cleaning, code quality checks, and Docker image builds for both Go and Python components. The specification ensures a standardized, efficient, and developer-friendly build interface with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios to verify proper implementation of all build targets and features.\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Makefile structure and organization\n18: \n19: The system SHALL implement a modular Makefile structure with a main Makefile in the root directory and organized sub-Makefiles for different language and functional areas.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Root Makefile exists and is properly structured\n22: - **GIVEN** the AgentCube project root directory\n23: - **WHEN** examining the directory structure\n24: - **THEN** a Makefile SHALL exist in the root directory\n25: - **AND** the Makefile SHALL be the main entry point for all build operations\n26: - **AND** the Makefile SHALL include sub-Makefiles from .makefiles/ directory\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: .makefiles/ directory exists with sub-Makefiles\n29: - **GIVEN** the .makefiles/ directory\n30: - **WHEN** examining its contents\n31: - **THEN** go.mk SHALL exist for Go-specific build rules\n32: - **AND** python.mk SHALL exist for Python-specific build rules\n33: - **AND** docker.mk SHALL exist for Docker-specific build rules\n34: - **AND** test.mk SHALL exist for test-specific rules\n35: - **AND** lint.mk SHALL exist for lint/format-specific rules\n36: - **AND** each sub-Makefile SHALL be properly included in the main Makefile\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: scripts/ directory exists for build scripts\n39: - **GIVEN** the scripts/ directory\n40: - **WHEN** examining its contents\n41: - **THEN** build.sh SHALL exist for complex build operations\n42: - **AND** test.sh SHALL exist for test execution scripts\n43: - **AND** release.sh SHALL exist for release preparation scripts\n44: - **AND** scripts SHALL be executable (chmod +x)\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: bin/ directory exists for build artifacts\n47: - **GIVEN** the bin/ directory\n48: - **WHEN** examining its structure\n49: - **THEN** the directory SHALL exist or be created on first build\n50: - **AND** the directory SHALL be in .gitignore\n51: - **AND** build artifacts SHALL be placed in bin/ by default\n52: - **AND** cross-platform artifacts SHALL be placed in bin/<platform>/ subdirectories\n53: \n54: ### Requirement: Go build targets\n55: \n56: The system SHALL provide comprehensive build targets for all Go binaries in the AgentCube project.\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: build-go target builds all Go binaries\n59: - **GIVEN** a clean AgentCube project with Go source code\n60: - **WHEN** running `make build-go`\n61: - **THEN** all Go binaries SHALL be compiled successfully\n62: - **AND** binaries SHALL be placed in bin/ directory\n63: - **AND** the following binaries SHALL be built: agentd, picod, cli\n64: - **AND** build status SHALL be displayed with color-coded output\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: build target builds both Go and Python components\n67: - **GIVEN** a clean AgentCube project\n68: - **WHEN** running `make build`\n69: - **THEN** `make build-go` SHALL be invoked\n70: - **AND** `make build-python` SHALL be invoked\n71: - **AND** both Go and Python artifacts SHALL be built successfully\n72: - **AND** the build SHALL complete without errors\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: Individual Go component build targets exist\n75: - **GIVEN** the Makefile Go targets\n76: - **WHEN** examining the available targets\n77: - **THEN** build-agentd target SHALL exist\n78: - **AND** build-picod target SHALL exist\n79: - **AND** build-router target SHALL exist (if router exists)\n80: - **AND** build-cli target SHALL exist\n81: - **AND** each target SHALL build only its respective component\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: build-agentd target builds agentd binary\n84: - **GIVEN** the agentd source code in cmd/agentd/\n85: - **WHEN** running `make build-agentd`\n86: - **THEN** agentd binary SHALL be compiled\n87: - **AND** the binary SHALL be placed at bin/agentd\n88: - **AND** the binary SHALL be executable\n89: - **AND** build metadata (version, commit) SHALL be embedded\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: build-picod target builds picod binary\n92: - **GIVEN** the picod source code in cmd/picod/\n93: - **WHEN** running `make build-picod`\n94: - **THEN** picod binary SHALL be compiled\n95: - **AND** the binary SHALL be placed at bin/picod\n96: - **AND** the binary SHALL be executable\n97: - **AND** build metadata SHALL be embedded\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: build-cli target builds CLI tool\n100: - **GIVEN** the CLI source code in cmd/cli/\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 959. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系 Delta Specification\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-033\n- **Title**: Makefile 构建目标体系\n- **Module**: root\n- **Language**: Makefile\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for the Makefile build target system in the AgentCube project. It defines requirements for a unified build system that manages building, testing, cleaning, code quality checks, and Docker image builds for both Go and Python components. The specification ensures a standardized, efficient, and developer-friendly build interface with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios to verify proper implementation of all build targets and features.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Makefile structure and organization\n\nThe system SHALL implement a modular Makefile structure with a main Makefile in the root directory and organized sub-Makefiles for different language and functional areas.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775886436029,"end":1775886436050}}}}
